1:1 COMMENT "# numeric_dissect.z -- compile-time dissection of a numeric-value generic"
1:74 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# parameter. `match cap` (bare), `match this.cap` (receiver access), and"
2:73 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `match (b.cap)` (another instance's access) all select a code path by the"
3:76 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# parameter's concrete VALUE at monomorphisation; only the matching arm"
4:72 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# survives in the generated C (the zerolang analogue of #ifdef over a"
5:70 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# compile-time constant). An `else` handles the unmatched values."
